---
description: Binding Omytea-Almighty Git, visibility, and publication contract
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `ORG-SYNC.md` before working. Canonical remote:
`Omytea-Almighty/omytea-personal-console`. Commit only deliberately reviewed paths. The
post-commit transport may push that existing commit, but must never stage,
commit, pull, merge, rebase, force-push, delete refs, change visibility, use
`git push --no-verify`, or bypass managed sync, security, publication, or
release gates. A repository-local `git commit --no-verify` exception is allowed
only when the repository's documented hook policy expressly permits it and the
operator records why. On any mismatch, preserve the local commit and report
`BLOCKED_*`.
